column_description: The ID of the panel.
The name of the variable.
The clean name of the variable.
The viability percentage.
The MFI reportable marker.
The cell count.
The flag indicating if the cell count is valid or not. Possible values are 'FALSE' and 'TRUE'.
The parent population.
The parent cell count.
The flag indicating if the parent cell count is valid or not. Possible values are 'FALSE' and 'TRUE'.

The original result unit raw. Possible values are 'percent_parent', 'median', '% CD4-CD8- of Lymphocytes', 'Freq. of Lymphocytes (%)', 'Freq. of CD45+ Live (%)', 'CD37 ABC on CD19+', '% CD19+CD20+CD24-CD38- of CD19+ OR CD20+ B Cells', '% T1&T2 CD19+CD20+CD24+CD38+CD27-CD10+ of CD19+ OR CD20+ B Cells', '% CD45 Live  of Single Cells'.
The flag indicating if the result is valid or not. Possible values are 'FALSE' and 'TRUE'.
The visit timepoint.
The study.
The ID of the study participant in the sample list.
The dummy group for safety events. Possible values are 'Group 0', 'Group 1', and 'Group 2'.
The dummy group for response. Possible values are 'Group X' and 'Group Y'.
The ID of the accession.
The standardized clean name of the variable.
The subtype of T cell.
The major T cell population. Possible values are 'CD4+' and 'CD8+'.
The short name of the T cell population. Possible values are 'central memory T cells', 'Temra T cells', 'effector memory T cells', 'naive T cells', 'Tregs', and 'parent T cells'.
The abbreviation of the T cell population. Possible values are 'cm', 'Temra', 'naive', 'em', 'Tregs', and 'parent'.
The value of the variable.
